BASEBALL - YANKEES CF BERNIE WILLIAMS PLACED ON DISABLED LIST . New York Yankees centre fielder Bernie Williams , originally expected to miss only the three - game series with the cross - town rival Mets , Tuesday was placed on the 15 - day disabled list with a strained left hamstring . Williams , who said he " felt something pop " while running out a groundball in the ninth inning of the Yankees ' 6 - 5 loss to Florida Sunday night , will be sidelined for the rest of the month . The Most Valuable Player of the 1996 American League Championship Series ( ALCS ) , Williams is hitting . 317 with 10 homers and 50 RBI in 66 games . The 28 - year - old switch - hitter enjoyed a breakout season in helping the Yankees win the World Series last season . In 1996 he posed career highs with 108 runs , 168 hits , 29 homers and 102 RBI while batting . 305 . Williams hit . 474 ( 9 - for - 19 ) with two homers and six RBI in the Yankees ' five - game ALCS victory over Baltimore that propelled New York into the World Series against Atlanta . The only player in baseball history to homer from both sides of the plate in the same post - season game , Williams did it for a second time in Game 4 of the first - round playoff series against Texas last season . He first accomplished the feat against Seattle in Game 3 of the 1995 playoffs . 
